text: Gan Ching Hwee (born 22 July 2003) is a Singaporean swimmer. She competed in the women's 1500 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. She won the women's 800m freestyle in the Liberty Insurance 50th Singapore National Age Group Swimming Championships and broke her own U-17 national record at 8:42.23. ==References== Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:Singaporean female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Competitors at the 2019 Southeast Asian Games Category:Southeast Asian Games gold medalists for Singapore Category:Southeast Asian Games silver medalists for Singapore Category:Southeast Asian Games medalists in swimming Category:Female freestyle swimmers
